David Robinson, the film critic for The Times of London who made
the final bid on behalf of the museum.
   Bidding began at $5,580 and quickly soared as a model wearing
the dress shimmied around to the music of ``Running Wild,'' which
Miss Monroe sang in the 1959 film.
   The dress was sold by the owner of a museum that closed in
Warwick, England.
