<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>Dukakis, Facing Budget Woes At Home, Takes Top Budget Aide On Road</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W. Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis,
whose budget problems at home have become an issue in his
presidential campaign, took his top state budget aide on the road
this week.
   Massachusetts Secretary of Administration and Finance Frank
Keefe accompanied Dukakis to New Jersey and New York on Wednesday
night and remained with the governor for campaign swings Thursday
through West Virginia and Nebraska. Both states hold presidential
primaries on Tuesday.
   Dukakis has been forced to roll back funding this fiscal year
because revenue collections are running below projections and also
has said he will be forced to trim spending his proposed budget for
the fiscal year beginning July 1.
   ``We've been able to get a little work done on the plane between
stops,'' Keefe said. He declined to be more specific.
   Keefe, one of the governor's top statehouse advisers, said he
had been planning for some time to take a campaign trip with
Dukakis.
</TEXT>
