<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0439</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Winds Stir Over California, Colorado and New Mexico</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Winds whipped southeast California, eastern Colorado and much of
New Mexico today while snow dusted the mountains of southwest
Nevada. Rain and thunderstorms prevailed over most of the nation.
   Wind advisories remained over southeast California where winds
gusted up to 35 mph on Thursday, and high wind watches were posted
today over much of New Mexico as well as the eastern foothills of
Colorado.
   Winds diminished over northwest Kansas, after gusting to 63 mph
on Thursday night.
   Snow was scattered over the mountains of southwest Nevada into
the early morning hours today. Showers fell along much of the
Oregon coast. Thunderstorms were widely scattered across western
Texas. Rain reached from Ohio, across southern New York state and
southern New England, across Pennsylvania and the Virginias.
   Today's weather forecast called for thunderstorms over portions
of western Texas; showers and thunderstorms from western Montana to
north-central Utah, from the northern Pacific coast across the
northern two-thirds of the Rockies and the northern Plains; rain
from the southern New England coast across the mid Atlantic coast;
winds strong and gusty from the southern two-thirds of the Rockies
across the central and northern Plains.
   High temperatures were forecast to be in the 50s from the
northern half of the Pacific coast across the Great Basin, also
from southern New England across the mid Atlantic coast; in the
upper 30s and 40s from east-central Nevada into the northern
Arizona mountains; in the 80s from the southern High Plains through
the central Plains, the lower half of the Missouri Valley and from
the lower two-thirds of the Mississippi Valley across Florida; in
the 90s over most of Texas and in the 60s and 70s over the rest of
the nation.
    Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 29
degrees at Klamath Falls, Ore., to 76 degrees at Del Rio, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 54 fair; Boston 52 foggy; Buffalo 54 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 57 fair; Cincinnati 52 fair; Miami 64 fair; New
York 56 foggy; Pittsburgh 53 foggy; Portland, Maine 52 cloudy;
Washington 56 rain.
   _Central: Chicago 57 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 64 fair; Des Moines
55 partly cloudy; Indianapolis 53 fair; Kansas City 60 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 61 fair; Nashville 52 fair; New Orleans 56
fair; St. Louis 59 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 60 fair; Anchorage 42 cloudy; Las Vegas 49
windy; Los Angeles 53 windy; Phoenix 63 fair; San Diego 55 fair;
San Francisco 50 windy.
   _Canada: Montreal 59 partly cloudy; Toronto 52 hazy.
</TEXT>
