<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Germany-Escape     05-06 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Germany-Escape,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two East Germans Flee To West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HANOVER, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two East Germans, one a uniformed
soldier, crept past border guards before dawn today and escaped
into West Germany, police said.
   The soldier was on guard duty and armed with a pistol when he
made his escape, said to Rainer Leonard, a spokesman for the West
German Border Police Command in Hanover.
   He identified the soldier as a sergeant who served with a border
unit and identified his companion as a construction worker. He said
the solider was posted by a 10-foot-high fence along the border at
the time of the escape.
   Police declined to release the names of the two East Germans or
provide other details of the escape according to regulations.
   The escapes brought the number of people fleeing communist East
Germany to West Germany this year to 38.
</TEXT>
