<HEAD>British Soldier Killed, 16 Injured in Mortar Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mortar shell exploded among British
troops on maneuvers Friday, killing one soldier and injuring 16, a
military spokesman said.
   The blast occurred in the northeastern Akamas peninsula while
British troops were carrying out routine exercises, said the
British bases spokesman, Maj. Johnny Rogers.
   He said the cause of the blast was under investigation and there
