<HEAD>Space Shuttle Emergency Landing Rescue Simulated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Space center rescue and medical
workers rehearsed procedures Friday for retrieving astronauts from
a space shuttle damaged during an emergency landing.
   A wooden mockup of an orbiter was used in the exercise, which
simulated a landing in a remote area off the runway.
   In the test, controlled from the launch control center,
helicopters were dispatched to pick up personnel representing the
astronauts, who then were transported to a nearby site for any
needed medical treatment.
   It was the second test here this week of space shuttle emergency
procedures. On Wednesday, seven astronauts and several workers fled
to safety, with some of them receiving make-believe injuries,
following a mock fire and explosion on the shuttle launch pad.
