<2ND_LINE>PM-Germany-US Crash, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0634,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>U.S. Military Helicopter Crashes At Air Show</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with two killed, CORRECTS that
helicopter is British but U.S.-made. No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HANOVER, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A British military helicopter
crashed and burst into flames at an international air show today,
killing at least two people and injuring several others, officials
said.
   Airport officials in Hanover said the crash occurred as the
helicopter returned from a short demonstration flight. They said
the helicopter hit a loading ramp at the airport with its back
rotor.
   In early reports, eyewitnesses said the helicopter belonged to
the U.S. military, but airport officials later said the aircraft
was a U.S.-made Chinook helicopter flown by the British.
   The accident occurred at about 6 p.m. (12 noon EDT) shortly
after the end of the air show, officials said.
   It was not immediately known whether the dead were members of
the crew or whether there were fatalities on the ground.
   Fire and emergency crews raced to the scene after the crash,
pouring foam on the burning wreckage.
</TEXT>
