<HEAD>One Swimmer Drowns During Strait Crossing, Three Hospitalized</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One swimmer drowned and three were hospitalized
after attempting to swim across a 21-mile-wide strait in southern
China, a newspaper reported.
   Thursday's Wen Hui Bao newspaper said Lo Qingshan drowned about
1,000 yards from shore while trying to swim across the Qiongzhou
Strait, between Guangdong province and the island province of
Hainan.
   The report accused organizers of the May 1 athletic event of
negligence. It did not name the organizers.
   The newspaper said the 38 swimmers were not given food or drink
during the 13-hour swim and that many climbed aboard boats halfway
across the strait because of cold and hunger.
   Officials from the provincial sports commission said the event
was held without their approval and that the organizers had no idea
of the dangers involved.
