<HEAD>Farm Workers To Get 20-30 Percent Wage Increases</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nearly 60,000 Cuban agricultural workers will
get wage increases of 20-30 percent during the summer months to
increase the food supply, Cuba's Prensa Latina news agency said
Friday.
   The report received in Mexico City said the decision was made by
the State Committee of Labor and Social Security and the increases
would be for the months of June, July and August when manual farm
work is heaviest.
   Prensa Latina said the measure's purpose is to increase the
harvest of vegetables and other foodstuffs during the summer
because of difficult weather conditions later in the year.
   It said the increases for Agriculture Ministry workers in
grains, vegetables and citrus fruits will be 30 percent in the city
of Havana and surrounding Havana province and 20 percent elsewhere
in Cuba.
