<1ST_LINE>r i AM-ItalyCustoms     05-06 0132</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Italy Customs,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Customs Officers' Protest Stops Thousands of Trucks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thousands of trucks were backed up Friday at
Italian crossing points on the borders with France, Switzerland,
Austria and Yugoslavia as Italian customs officers refused to work
overtime.
   A meeting between union and government oficials failed to
resolve the dispute. Further talks were scheduled for Tuesday.
   Hundreds of truck drivers blocked the Milan_Chiasso highway on
the Italian-Swiss border to protest delays in clearing freight
documents.
   Police reported thousands of trucks lined up at other crossings
and said automobile traffic was badly delayed.
   About 5,000 customs officers are refusing to examine freight
documents after the end of their regular work hours at 2 p.m. to
press their demands for pay increases and a reorganization of the
customs system.
</TEXT>
