<HEAD>Five Killed In Fiery Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LENEXA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A dump truck pulling a tractor on a flatbed
trailer Friday jumped the median and crashed into a car and van on
Interstate 35 in suburban Kansas City, killing five people and
injuring four, police said.
   The truck hit an oncoming car carrying a woman and three
children, the Kansas Highway Patrol said. The car burst into
flames, and all inside were killed. The driver of the van also
died, said Sgt. Robert Sharp.
   A taxi collided with the other vehicles during the accident,
injuring the cab driver and two passengers. The truck driver also
was injured, Sharp said.
   The injured were treated at a hospital and released, he said.
   The 2:30 p.m. accident closed the southbound lanes of the
highway for about four hours, according to Sharp.
