<DOCNO> AP880506-0252 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-05-06-88 0017EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f PM-MutualFundFootnotes     05-06 0357</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Mutual Fund Footnotes,0370</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Footnotes Expanded for AP Mutual Fund Lists</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mutual fund lists appearing in newspapers are
carrying some new footnotes.
   Because of the growing complexity and variation in commissions,
dividends and fees for mutual funds, The Associated Press has
revised the footnotes it uses to denote those aspects of funds.
   For instance, an ``NL'' designation in place of an offering
price is being used in the daily list now only when a mutual fund
truly is ``no load'' _ that is, there is no sales commission to buy
into the fund or to redeem shares and get out.
   The weekly mutual fund tables will denote no-load funds with an
``n'' footnote after the name.
   Some funds do not charge a commission when you buy shares but do
charge a fee if the shares are sold within a certain period, a
condition called a contingent-deferred-sales charge. Those funds
are shown having an offering price the same as the net asset value
(NAV) and carry a new footnote _ ``r'' _ after the name of the fund.
   Some funds charge an annual fee to cover marketing expenses,
although they do not include the charge in their advertised sales
fee. That condition is denoted with a ``p'' footnote following the
fund name.
   Funds that both have a contingent-deferred-sales charge and
charge a percentage of fund assets for marketing expenses now carry
a ``t'' footnote.
   Footnotes also have been changed for denoting ex-dividend,
ex-distribution and stock split or stock dividends.
   Previously, all those conditions were represented by an ``x''
footnote. Now ``x'' designates an ex-dividend, ``e'' means
ex-distribution of capital gains and ``s'' denotes a stock split or
stock dividend.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Here is the explanation of the footnotes for the mutual funds
list:
   e _ Ex capital gains distribution. s _ Stock dividend or split.
x _ Ex cash dividend.
   f _ Previous day's quote. (NL)n _ No frontend load or contingent
deferred sales load. p _ Fund assets are used to pay for
distribution costs-12(b)(1) plan. r _ Redemption fee or contingent
deferred sales load may apply. t _ Both p and r.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
