<FILEID>AP-NR-05-06-88 1415EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   05-06 0182</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Share Prices Rise</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: updates with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices on the London stock exchange rose
Friday, boosted by gains in early trading on Wall Street and a
flurry of markups after the start of a new trading account.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index
rose 11.6 points, or 0.64 percent, to 1801.1.
   Speculative stocks remained in the spotlight, accounting for
much of the day's trading volume and the major stock price moves.
   But dealers also reported some new institutional buying
interest. A bullish report on the British equity market, issued by
Nomura Research Institute, gave a boost to investor sentiment, they
said. The report also was perceived as encouraging Japanese
investors to invest in London, they said.
   Later, shares gained some more when Wall Street shrugged off
mixed signals about the U.S. economy in the form of unemployment
data for April. And the start of a new two-week trading account
brought a wave of markups by market makers, with virtually no
selling pressure to bring prices back down, dealers said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
