<1ST_LINE>r f BC-USF&G-Citicorp     05-06 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-USF&G-Citicorp,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>USF&G Financial Services Acquiring Citicorp Investment Management</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USF&G Financial Services Corp. agreed Friday to
acquire Citicorp Investment Management of New York for $102.5
million.
   Citicorp Investment Management, the domestic institutional
investment advisory unit of Citicorp, has approximately $18 billion
in assets under management.
   The majority of Citicorp Investment Management employees are
located in New York, with others in San Francisco, Houston, and
Chicago. USF&G said they are expected to remain in those locations.
   Citicorp Investment Management offers fixed income and equity
funds. The company is involved in portfolio management,
relationship management, research analysis, sales and trading; its
clients are within the institutional market, primarily pension
funds and benefits plans.
   USF&G Financial Services Corp., through its subsidiaries, is
engaged in investment management and advisory services; real estate
investment services; pension consulting; and strategic planning and
consulting.
   It is a subsidiary of USF&G Corp., a holding company for
property, casualty and life insurance subsidiaries as well as
financial services.
</TEXT>
